          Wix has been around since 2006. 200+ million sites. Every edge case is handled. Framer is newer with some rough edges. If you want battle-tested reliability, Wix wins.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6 flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#8B5CF6]"></div>So which should you use?
        </h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Framer if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You want modern design with animations</li>
          <li>You like AI generation</li>
          <li>PageSpeed matters to you</li>
          <li>You want a clean, fast site</li>
          <li>You do not need hundreds of apps</li>
          <li>You're building marketing sites or portfolios</li>
          <li>You have technical tolerance for integrations</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Choose Wix if:</h3>
        <ul class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          <li>You want to pick from hundreds of templates</li>
          <li>You need specific apps and integrations</li>
          <li>You want an established platform</li>
          <li>You do not care about PageSpeed</li>
          <li>You want the most features possible</li>
          <li>You're building restaurants, booking-heavy sites</li>
          <li>You need 24/7 phone support</li>
